What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Aniline Derivatives Market?

Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Aniline Derivatives Market

The aniline derivatives market is expected to witness market growth at a rate of 6.10% in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028, and will reach the value of USD 9,500 million by 2028. Data Bridge Market Research report on aniline derivatives market provides analysis and insights regarding the various factors expected to be prevalent throughout the forecast period while providing their impacts on the marketâ€™s growth. The increase in demand for the product for various industrial applications is escalating the growth of aniline derivatives market.

Aniline refers to the simplest of the principal aromatic amines and looks yellowish to brownish oily liquid with a musty fishy odor in physical attributes. The derivatives of aniline are widely utilized in manufacturing of rubber, dyes & pigments, photographic chemicals, polymers, agricultural chemicals, and pharmaceuticals. These derivatives are produced by hydrogenation of their nitro aromatic precursors.

The increase in demand of aniline for gasoline and anti-knock additives across the globe acts as one of the major factors driving the growth of aniline derivatives market. The rise in demand for aniline by various end-use industries as a raw material in the production of several end-products, and surge in manufacturing of aniline due to the favorable policies government accelerate the market growth. The increase in for demand for plastics in the medical industry for manufacturing medical devices such as masks, catheters, tubes, and bags, and high use as an intermediate for dyes, agrochemicals, and several organic products further influence the market. Additionally, increase in research and development activities in the petroleum industry, rise in automotive sales, and adoption of aniline by automotive manufacturers for the production of methylene diphenyl diisocyanate foams positively affect the aniline derivatives market. Furthermore, use as anti-corrosive nature in various end-use industries extends profitable opportunities to the market players in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028.

On the other hand, high volatility in raw material prices and complex process are expected to obstruct the market growth. The negative impact of COVID-19 on manufacturing industries are projected to challenge the aniline derivatives market in the forecast period of 2021-2028.

